name: BrianFeroldi
tweet:
WACC is a benchmark for evaluating projects & acquisitions.

WACC is also the discount rate for future cash flows when performing a DCF analysis.

Investments, projects, & acquisitions should only proceed when the expected return is greater than WACC. https://t.co/PydCcAuEiQ

name: BrianFeroldi
tweet:
WACC = [(E/V) x Re] + [(D/V) x Rd x (1 - Tc)]

E = Market value of the firm‚Äôs equity
D = Market value of the firm‚Äôs debt
V = E + D
Re = Cost of equity
Rd = Cost of debt
Tc = Corporate tax rate

WACC is a sum of the weighting of each capital source https://t.co/mrBaXTCLkg

name: BrianFeroldi
tweet:
WACC is the average after-tax expense of capital for a company from all of its sources. 

This includes common stock, preferred stock, bonds, and other hybrid debt & equity instruments.

WACC is the mean rate a company pays to fund its operations. https://t.co/wr2i3blMfV

RISK MANAGEMENT WITH STOCKS
* Maintain 6 months of savings 
* Invest only your 5-year+ money
* No position > 20% of the portfolio
* Diversify across sectors
* Add money as often as you can

Then simulate a 40% decline for the portfolio and see how you feel.
